snippet.textDisplay:
According to the SCMP article, the "new Chinese Laser Assault Rifle" is:

A hand-held, 3kg, rechargeable lithium ion battery powered, 1000 shots per-charge laser rifle that supposedly ignites clothing at 800m...?

Nope! This is what you call: Fake News. Sorry China, you cannot invent your own physics.

What sort of small <3kg Li battery can hold enough power for lethal shots at 800m range and dealing 1000 shots on a charged battery? Impossible! They claim the entire system weighs 3kg, so the battery must weigh way less than 3kg. You cannot pack the required power into a battery that small. Even a 300kg battery couldn't do it.

The SCMP article talks of sub-2 second "shots" or beam dwell time, so who can aim a hand held weapon steady on a target 800m away for over 1 second to achieve a burn? No one!

What sort of optics and materials are they using that can handle 1000 x 1+ second lethal shots at 800m range, not melt or burst AND remain perfectly optically collimated in battlefield use? Pure magic or pure bullshit.
